What about having just a decision(bool, map) and you would call that with a emptyMap?
public static final Decision decision(boolean isSampled, Map<String, AttributeValue> attributes) {
  Objects.requireNotNull(attributes, "attributes");
  if (attributes.isEmpty()) {
    return isSampled ? EMPTY_SAMPLED_DECISION : EMPTY_NOT_SAMPLED_DECISION;
  }
  return DecisionImpl.create(isSampled, attributes);
}
